{
  "design_notes": "An easy-level chart designed to follow the energy curve of the track. Rhythms are primarily steady quarter notes with occasional eighth notes during high energy build-ups. Downbeat jumps are used very sparingly to highlight drop transitions, and hold notes are integrated naturally with 1.0 beat durations to meet the easy level budget. There are no crossovers or jacks, providing a highly comfortable and intuitive experience for beginner players.",
